The article discusses the Supreme Court's ruling in 303 Creative v. Elenis, which creates an exception to protections against discrimination in public accommodations. The author argues that this ruling allows businesses to discriminate in the name of "free expression" against marginalized communities such as the LGBTQI+ community, racial and religious minorities, the disability community, and women. The author emphasizes the importance of enforcing federal anti-discrimination protections and calls on Congress to pass the Equality Act.